Heat grill. Lightly sprinkle steaks with seasoning. Prepare hash browns according to package directions, except use 4 tablespoons of herb butter to melt in the pan and the remaining 2 tablespoons to dollop over top of hash browns before flipping. Remove from heat. Sprinkle with cheese and cover. When ready to grill, place steak over medium-high heat; cover. Cook for 8 to 10 minutes, turning once, until steak is cooked to desired doneness. Serve hash browns with steak.